    "text": "I need it right now :star-struck: How do you call it? (it's not part of vlojure, right?)\n\nBTW re shader authoring - if a shader has some controllable parameters, then it's possible to tune them automatically to match some target image. It's a fairly new thing still but IMO in a couple years it's going to change how we write shaders. Differentiable shaders today are where language models were in 2015. The only problem is that very few implementations exist right now (<https://pixl.cs.princeton.edu/pubs/Yang_2022_AAF/index.php> is one) and they still lack a good end-user tooling.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1768022428.254509",
