                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Its not very dense.\n\nI think the 2D planar layout is not actually correct for an edge graph. I have gone polar because it symmetrical. In runtime that supports cyclical imports, there is no clear meaning to the 2D plane: top, bottom, left or right. Polar gives everybody the same positional status and there is no boundary. You can cut the circle and unwrap to give a line, if you wanted to vertical layout."
